  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In the present study the main goal has been to clarify the effect of the probiotic bacteria
      Lactobacillus plantarum 299v on the salivary cortisol level in young adults under examination
      stress. Salivary IgA from minor glands and in whole human saliva was measured as alternative
      marker of stress. The hypothesis was that the levels of cortisol would be reduced or
      stabilized in the test group in comparison to the placebo group where the cortisol levels
      were expected to increase due to the examination-induced stress. By contrast, the salivary
      IgA levels were expected to increase in the test group in comparison to the placebo group.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
